    // guaranteed to be at least 4 bytes, it is often 8 bytes on 64-bit systems. This is a common
    // variation that highlights the 'typical' nature of the values in Table 2-6 and the importance
    // of the 'NOTE' about sizes varying by operating system/compiler. Programmers should use
    // `sizeof` or `std::numeric_limits` for precise information on their specific system
