2.  **`using namespace std;`**: This statement brings the `std` namespace into scope, so we can use `cout` directly without `std::` prefix.
3.  **`int main()`**: This is the entry point of the C++ program.
4.  **`long double apple;`**: A variable named `apple` is declared with the `long double` data type. This demonstrates how `sizeof` can be used with a variable name.
5.  **`cout << "The size of an integer is " << sizeof(int);`**: This line prints a descriptive string and then uses `sizeof(int)` to get the size of the `int` data type in bytes. The result is streamed to `cout`.
6.  **`cout << " bytes.\n";`**: This continues the output, adding " bytes." and a newline character for formatting.
7.  **`cout << "The size of a long integer is " << sizeof(long);`**: Similar to the `int` example, this line uses `sizeof(long)` to determine and print the size of the `long` data type.
8.  **`cout << " bytes.\n";`**: Adds the unit and newline.
9.  **`cout << "An apple can be eaten in " << sizeof(apple);`**: This line demonstrates using `sizeof` with a variable (`apple`) to find its size. The output will be the size of a `long double` on the system.
10. **`cout << " bytes!\n";`**: Completes the output for the `apple` variable.
11. **`return 0;`**: Indicates successful program execution.

