2.  **`int main()`**: The main function where program execution begins.
3.  **`cout << "Size of char: " << sizeof(char) << " byte(s)\n";`**: Uses `sizeof(char)` to get the size of the `char` data type, which is typically 1 byte.
4.  **`cout << "Size of float: " << sizeof(float) << " bytes\n";`**: Uses `sizeof(float)` to get the size of the `float` data type, typically 4 bytes.
5.  **`cout << "Size of double: " << sizeof(double) << " bytes\n";`**: Uses `sizeof(double)` to get the size of the `double` data type, typically 8 bytes.
